              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "3KORKOR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Hanyang Univ., Seoul"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USABRK"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "94-PU-244",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.986
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The target 215 micrograms of",
                "244Pu electrosprayed onto a 12.5 micrometers Be foil.",
                "The diameter was 6.3 mm yielding the average target",
                "thickness of 672 micrograms/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC",
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Beta proportional counter and alpha",
                "proportional counter were used to measure beta and",
                "alpha activities, respectively. Alpha pulse analysis",
                "of Pu sample was carried out using gold-plated",
                "surface barrier detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "B-",
                "A"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "BSPEC",
                "ASPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Reaction products were collected",
                "on the aluminum catcher foil and dissolved with 10M",
                "sodium hydroxide then removed rare earths and",
                "transition elements with lanthanide fluoride",
                "precipitation method. The residual alpha and beta",
                "activities were measured with proportional counters."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DECAY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " From the observed decay curves isotopes were",
                "identified. The cross section for each isotope was",
                "calculated as: sigma = m/(I*N*(1-exp(-lambda tb))*(1-",
                "exp(-lambda tc))*c*gc*gb), where m is counting rate",
                "after the cooling, I is intensity of Xe ion per min,",
                "N is initial counting rate, tb is bombardment time of",
                "244Pu target, tc is chemical separation and cooling",
                "time, lambda is decay const for each isotope, c is",
                "counting efficiency, gc is chemical yield for each",
                "element, gb is ratio of total activity to given",
                "activity."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
